64
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:08,510
﻿You tell him where to go. "No,
on second thought, turn around."

65
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,390
﻿It's loads of power. Loads.

66
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:18,590
﻿And... you try to do
what's right with it.

67
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,510
﻿Vertex to Snow White.

68
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:31,830
﻿Vertex, they're on your right,
running away towards the schools.

69
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:33,910
﻿Roger. I'm on my way.

70
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:40,710
﻿Vertex. they're heading, towards
Intersection 76.

71
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:42,790
﻿Vertex to Snow White.

72
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,990
﻿Vertex, did you identify them?

73
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:58,350
﻿There were some stone throwers
and I got them.

74
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:03,870
﻿So I had to go to HQ.
make a statement

75
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,870
﻿and identify them
from a lineup.

76
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,590
﻿And it's scary
and I stressed out.

77
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:18,030
﻿All the way there. I started
doubting myself. I thought:

78
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:23,910
﻿"Maybe they didn't throw stones.
I can't remember what happened..."

79
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:34,470
﻿When I got there.
I saw them tied up.

80
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:40,430
﻿blindfolded, real life size.
Real, living people.

81
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:45,790
﻿Then I went in to write
my witness' statement.

82
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:49,590
﻿with my lack of confidence.

83
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,590
﻿So I asked the investigator:

84
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:58,350
﻿"What if... Let's say...
it didn't happen?

85
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:01,070
﻿"If they don't confess,
will you release them?"

86
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:06,750
﻿He looked at me and said:

87
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,630
﻿"They will confess."

88
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:13,590
﻿So I said: "But what
if they didn't do it?"

89
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,670
﻿He said: "They'll confess."

90
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:27,710
﻿You think: "I have to be here,
I have to do this, but I can't.

91
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:30,870
﻿"How will they confess?
In what way?"

92
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:36,750
﻿But then you go back to base and
have to start your next shift.

93
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:39,550
﻿You have to.
What, you won't do it?

94
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:00,030
﻿That was the atmosphere:
taking the jeep.

95
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,270
﻿doors open in the back,
driving fast,

96
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:05,670
﻿skidding and spinning out.
I remember thinking:

97
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:11,070
﻿"We're in the Wild West.
We can do whatever we feel like."

98
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:15,590
﻿Part of doing what you
feel like was, for example.

99
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:18,270
﻿to stop our jeep
next to a group of people.

100
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:21,190
﻿call them over with our finger,
to approach...

101
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,990
﻿This power, that you
just motion with your finger

102
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:27,510
﻿and the person comes.
No hesitation.

103
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:36,630
﻿There was one time when
we released a boy in the Strip.

104
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:39,430
﻿In the evening.
That night.

105
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:43,230
﻿the commander was patrolling
in the area in a jeep

106
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:48,310
﻿and he saw the boy sitting in
a corner, at a soldiers' post

107
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,630
﻿and he asked the soldiers:

108
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,630
﻿"What's he doing here?
We let him go hours ago."

109
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:59,070
﻿So they said: "We were
just playing with him."

110
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:06,270
﻿He approached the boy who
was crying and hysterical

111
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,110
﻿and...

112
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:15,030
﻿He was in a very bad state.
All beaten up.

113
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,790
﻿The commander returned
to the War Room and said:

114
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:22,190
﻿"Call the commander who's
in charge of those soldiers.

115
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:27,230
﻿"I want a report
about this event."

116
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,070
﻿The report arrived
at the War Room

117
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:36,510
﻿and it detailed how the soldiers,
who didn't lie about it.

118
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,910
﻿specifically stated

119
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:43,190
﻿how they beat him up.
put out cigarettes on him. etc.

120
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,590
﻿I handed the report
to my commander

121
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:49,190
﻿and he said:

122
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:55,790
﻿"Call that commander,
tell him that with this report

123
00:12:55,840 --> 00:13:00,870
﻿"we'll have the
Investigation Unit all over us.

124
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,710
﻿"Tell him to change the report."

125
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:10,630
﻿I remember that 30-second walk

126
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:13,350
﻿from his office back
to the War Room.

127
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:17,870
﻿with the report in my hand.

128
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,790
﻿I think it was the only time
in my service

129
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:25,190
﻿that I thought about
contacting a journalist.

130
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:30,190
﻿This is my chance.
I’m about to get another report.

131
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:33,950
﻿I could show him both versions,
as proof.

132
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:38,630
﻿I deliberated whether
I should photocopy it

133
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:42,350
﻿before it gets "buried" away,
but I didn't do it.

134
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:51,750
﻿I called the said commander,
and told him:

135
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:58,070
﻿"You are required to...
write up a new report."

136
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:03,910
﻿He said: "No problem."
And we got a new report.

137
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:11,150
﻿I was thinking about it
all day long, the new report said:

138
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:14,910
﻿"The boy is a pathological liar,
he also claimed...

139
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:20,790
﻿"that the soldiers did
this and that to him...

140
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:23,310
﻿"The boy is a pathological liar,
the soldiers

141
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:29,470
﻿"treated him well, etc."
And that was the end of it.

142
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:40,550
﻿I was struggling to remain humane,
at least a little.

143
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:45,230
﻿In the reality that I was in.
it was completely wiped out.

144
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,590
﻿Why didn't I do it?

145
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,950
﻿Because...

146
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:05,590
﻿it was just a fantasy.
There was no chance that...

147
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:12,470
﻿I really don't know
why I didn't do it.

148
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:43,230
﻿Lions, lions...

149
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:48,270
﻿The volume is very high
in the Territories.

150
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:54,590
﻿Everyone yells.
With one another and...

151
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:59,950
﻿Like. "Hey. dude."
everybody talks like this.

152
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:03,310
﻿and it's funny that
you, as a girl.

153
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:07,310
﻿take on masculine traits.

154
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:11,350
﻿You find yourself
talking like a man.

155
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,750
﻿you hide
feminine characteristics.

156
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,070
﻿For instance,
it was very cold in Hebron.

157
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,630
﻿so I'd wear a winter jumpsuit.

158
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:22,310
﻿which makes you look
like a teddy bear.

159
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,910
﻿not like a boy or a girl.

160
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:27,830
﻿you try to hide your
feminine characteristics.

161
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:32,830
﻿Because everyone
knows you're a woman.

162
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:34,750
﻿that won't change.

163
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:38,430
﻿but to be "one of the guys",
to belong.

164
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:47,150
﻿I'd only been
there for 4 days.

165
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,150
﻿the first time I met
my soldiers.

166
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:52,390
﻿I was really excited,
everyone asked me who I was.

167
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:54,670
﻿a new girl,
very interesting.

168
00:16:54,960 --> 00:17:00,870
﻿Then I noticed that they
were holding prayer beads

169
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,270
﻿and little Korans.
So I said: "Wow. that's nice."

170
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:06,550
﻿"Where did you get those?"

171
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,510
﻿So they said:
"We brought them from Qalqilya."

172
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:15,470
﻿I was like. "What?
But that's looting. It's forbidden."

173
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:18,910
﻿And they said:
"It's okay, it's okay."

174
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,790
﻿A few days later.
I met with the regiment commander

175
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:26,630
﻿and he asked me: "What's
your impression of us so far?"

176
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:29,030
﻿I said: "The regiment
is wonderful.

177
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:32,710
﻿"everyone's great, but I
noticed that a certain company

178
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:36,350
﻿"took some beads and
Korans from Qalqilya

179
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,990
﻿"and perhaps you should
look into that."

180
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:43,910
﻿He says: "What? Are you sure?"
I say: "Yes."

181
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:48,990
﻿So he phones the
company commander and says:

182
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,110
﻿"The Education NCO is here
and she says that she saw

183
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,950
﻿"this and that
in your company."

184
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:55,950
﻿The commander says:
"She's a liar!"

185
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,270
﻿I was so shocked.
Then he says:

186
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,710
﻿"If it did happen.
it will be strictly dealt with."

187
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,910
﻿Ok.

188
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,990
﻿A few days later. I went
to visit that company

189
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:07,790
﻿and its commander saw me.
He says:

190
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:11,950
﻿"So you're the Education NCO
who squealed on us?"

191
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:16,190
﻿And then
his soldiers started...

192
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:21,710
﻿I can't even describe it...
They banned me.

193
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:24,270
﻿They wouldn't let me into
their company for 4 months.

194
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:27,390
﻿If they saw me walk by.
they'd spit on the ground.

195
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,950
﻿I really regretted
having done that:

196
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:50,790
﻿From now on. if they're just
little things. I'll keep quiet.

197
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:55,110
﻿Your social status in the
regiment is very important.

198
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:58,350
﻿You're supposed to be the
sweet girl that everyone likes.

199
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,190
﻿who who keeps them company
and whose hair smells good.

200
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:04,230
﻿It's a very cushy job.

201
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:09,310
﻿All you have to do is wash
your hair every so often.

202
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:41,030
﻿I loved the guys,
they were great.

203
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:42,870
﻿I was a real queen there.

204
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:45,630
﻿I was a blonde,
and in our unit...

205
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,750
﻿Blondes get respect!

206
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,630
﻿There was a sick
sense of humor.

207
00:19:56,680 --> 00:20:00,630
﻿We were nearby a mosque.

208
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:03,070
﻿when suddenly we hear
from the mosque:

209
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,710
﻿"I've Got the Power!"

210
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:08,790
﻿It's that song...
I don't remember how...

211
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:10,790
A very funny old song.

212
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,070
﻿Instead of "Allah is Great",
you hear: "I've Got the Power!"

213
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:16,110
﻿They just went up
to the mosque.

214
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,830
﻿changed the tapes,
and that was that.

215
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:23,110
﻿It was great,
it was a joke that...

216
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,070
﻿Whoever did it.
and I know who did.

217
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:31,470
﻿they were awesome!
What a brilliant thing to do!

218
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,510
﻿We really enjoyed
this adrenaline, the action.

219
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:51,590
﻿If there was an incident
on your shift, you felt lucky.

220
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,430
﻿It felt like...

221
00:20:55,480 --> 00:21:00,750
﻿you were watching a soccer game
that you can't see.

222
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:03,710
﻿You wait for the
next big thing to happen.

223
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,270
﻿We'd turn the volume of
all the radios to the maximum

224
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,150
﻿and...

225
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,310
﻿"Well? Well?"

226
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:17,390
﻿Then there's a huge boom that
shakes the whole War Room.

227
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:21,150
﻿mission accomplished,
the house is destroyed.

228
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,270
﻿To get the best view point

229
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,870
﻿we'd run to the canteen
and climb up on the...

230
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,390
﻿picnic-style tables
that they had there.

231
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:34,270
﻿to see beyond the wall
really clearly.

232
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:37,430
﻿how Beit Hanun
was being attacked.

233
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:01,950
﻿In one of the operations,
two terrorists dressed up as women.

234
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:05,990
﻿Male soldiers
couldn't touch women.

235
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,710
﻿They weren't checked
and discovered

236
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,670
